WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.320
What brought me specifically to Kitchens for Good

00:00:02.320 --> 00:00:05.640
was actually looking for a job during the height

00:00:05.640 --> 00:00:07.840
of the COVID pandemic.

00:00:07.840 --> 00:00:10.960
And I really wanted to make sure I'm working

00:00:10.960 --> 00:00:14.040
for an organization that I feel so passionately about.

00:00:14.040 --> 00:00:17.640
And when I came across Kitchens for Good's job posting,

00:00:17.640 --> 00:00:21.780
I knew that I had found the thing that I could do

00:00:21.780 --> 00:00:24.900
and become even more passionate about.

00:00:24.900 --> 00:00:27.000
I had a grandfather who was a cook.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:28.000
He was a cook in the Navy.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:30.040
And he ran hospital kitchens.

00:00:30.040 --> 00:00:35.040
And he always spoke about giving people a chance

00:00:35.240 --> 00:00:37.880
that might not otherwise have an opportunity.

00:00:37.880 --> 00:00:41.840
And that kitchens were the perfect place

00:00:41.840 --> 00:00:45.040
to get people started and to give them second chances.

00:00:45.040 --> 00:00:48.100
So it just felt completely serendipitous.

00:00:48.100 --> 00:00:50.600
And like, this is where I'm supposed to be,

00:00:50.600 --> 00:00:53.040
even if it was kind of a crazy time in the world

00:00:53.040 --> 00:00:54.520
and in my life as well.

00:00:54.520 --> 00:00:57.840
Every day, you know, he was a big part of my life.

00:00:58.680 --> 00:00:59.600
And I did spend a lot of time with him.

00:00:59.600 --> 00:01:03.200
And so it wasn't something that I understood at that time

00:01:03.200 --> 00:01:05.360
when I was with him.

00:01:05.360 --> 00:01:08.600
It just kind of took up a space in the back of my brain.

00:01:08.600 --> 00:01:11.080
And so to really be living that now,

00:01:11.080 --> 00:01:12.800
I mean, I think about him every single day

00:01:12.800 --> 00:01:14.000
that I'm doing this work.
